
  Name:  _Exit
  
  #include <stdlib.h>
  void _Exit(int exit_code);
  
  _Exit( ) was added by C99.
  The _Exit( ) function is similar to exit( ) except for :
  -> No calls to termination functions registered by atexit( )
     are made.
  -> No calls to signal handlers registered by signal( ) are made.
  -> Open files are not necessarily flushed or closed.
  
  Related Functions:  atexit, abort and exit

